{
  "status": "ok",
  "message": [
    "This is the box <%= box_name %>, a Unix shell account for the project.",
    "",
    "a) SSH access",
    "Add your SSH public key with the web API.",
    "curl --data-urlencode sshkey@$(printf ~/.ssh/id_[rd]sa.pub) --data apikey=<apikey> <%= rooturl %>/<%= box_name %>/sshkeys",
    "Then connect (notice you should use a . instead of a /):",
    "ssh <%= user_name %>@<%= server_hostname %>",
    "",
    "b) git repository",
    "Each box has its own git repository in the /home/ directory.",
    "Initially it contains a README.md file for describing the project",
    "and a scraperwiki.json file for configuring it.",
    "",
    "c) Web server",
    "The box can serve static files in public. Put them in a",
    "directory called http/ inside the box. They will be served",
    "here (over either http or https):",
    <% if (publish_token) { %>
    "https://<%= server_hostname %>/<%= box_name %>/<%= publish_token %>/http",
    <% } else { %>
    "https://<%= server_hostname %>/<%= box_name %>/http",
    <% } %>
    "You can serve JSON files as JSONP by appending a ?callback parameter to your request.",
    "",
    "d) Scheduling",
    "Set a crontab using the crontab(1) command just like on any Unix.",
    "shell account. e.g. crontab -e",
    "",
    "e) SQL over HTTP API",
    "Specify the name of an SQLite file by adding an entry",
    "'database' in scraperwiki.json. You can then query the",
    "database with SQL over HTTP to get JSON using this URL:",
    <% if (publish_token) { %>
    "https://<%= server_hostname %>/<%= box_name %>/<%= publish_token %>/sqlite",
    <% } else { %>
    "https://<%= server_hostname %>/<%= box_name %>/sqlite",
    <% } %>
    "Parameters are:",
    "q= SQL query to execute",
    "callback= (optional) return results as JSONP of specified variable",
    "",
    "f) Read only file API",
    "Specify the file's path you want to read by using this URL:",
    "https://<%= server_hostname %>/<%= box_name %>/files/<file path>?apikey=<apikey>",
    "",
    "g) Restrict access to your data using a publishing token",
    "By default, a publish_token is generated, which is required to access your",
    "http files or sqlite API. If you would like to disable or edit this,",
    "remove the publish_token field from your scraperwiki.json",
    "The token must be alphanumeric and between 10-30 characters",
    "",
    "f) Command execution API",
    "Specify the command to execute by POSTing your 'apikey' and 'cmd' to:",
    "https://<%= server_hostname %>/<%= box_name %>/exec"
  ]
}
